WEBVTT

00:02.503 --> 00:04.705
Ostensibly on Legion...

00:04.738 --> 00:08.076
NARRATOR: A delusion starts
like any other idea, as an egg.

00:08.109 --> 00:12.012
From the shell, you'd never
know anything was wrong.

00:12.046 --> 00:15.383
It's what's inside
that matters.

00:17.685 --> 00:20.221
You're still working for him.

00:20.254 --> 00:21.722
-The Shadow King.
-Okay,

00:21.755 --> 00:24.192
I'm not not working for him.

00:24.225 --> 00:25.993
How are you real?

00:29.097 --> 00:30.664
Whose body is that?

00:30.698 --> 00:32.366
LENNY: I'm not sure
Farouk found his body.

00:34.034 --> 00:36.003
I think he found mine.

00:36.036 --> 00:38.139
:
No, no, no, no.

00:45.313 --> 00:47.315
*

01:11.572 --> 01:16.110
NARRATOR: Moral panic is defined
as "public anxiety or alarm

01:16.144 --> 01:18.112
"in response
to a perceived threat

01:18.146 --> 01:20.648
to the moral standards
of society."

01:25.586 --> 01:28.489
The road to moral panic

01:28.522 --> 01:32.726
has several stops.

01:32.760 --> 01:36.464
The first is concern.

01:40.434 --> 01:45.439
This concern, limited at first,

01:45.473 --> 01:48.342
spreads from person
to person...

01:54.848 --> 01:57.351
...amplified
by cultural forces...

02:02.490 --> 02:06.160
...until rational concern

02:06.194 --> 02:09.163
becomes irrational fear.

02:11.799 --> 02:13.301
People come to believe

02:13.334 --> 02:15.169
something terrible
is happening.

02:15.203 --> 02:18.506
Something they cannot see.

02:18.539 --> 02:20.874
That they can't control.

02:27.315 --> 02:30.184
It has come for others.

02:30.218 --> 02:33.120
It will come for them.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.288
:
Witch!

02:34.322 --> 02:36.324
Get her!

02:39.860 --> 02:43.297
NARRATOR: Whether or not
the threat is real,

02:43.331 --> 02:46.734
the response certainly is.

02:46.767 --> 02:50.771
And it is often excessive.

03:09.189 --> 03:11.392
Ask yourself:

03:11.425 --> 03:15.563
what's more terrifying,

03:15.596 --> 03:19.767
fear, or the frightened?

04:57.831 --> 05:00.000
DAVID :
Amahl Farouk,

05:00.033 --> 05:05.773
tapeworm, parasite, shit beetle.

05:05.806 --> 05:08.642
I'm calling you out.

05:08.676 --> 05:10.678
*

05:32.065 --> 05:34.402
You're upset.

05:41.742 --> 05:43.377
Use your words.

05:45.413 --> 05:47.381
Amy.

05:47.415 --> 05:48.982
Oh, please.

05:49.016 --> 05:51.752
She put you in l'asile,
like a crazy person.

05:51.785 --> 05:53.654
I was sick.

05:53.687 --> 05:57.658
You were a joke, something
to laugh at with her friends.

05:57.691 --> 05:59.059
David the dancing bear.

06:00.794 --> 06:05.365
She was trying to help me,
and you killed her.

06:09.369 --> 06:11.338
Did she?

06:11.371 --> 06:12.906
Help?

06:12.940 --> 06:18.679
Or did you wish horrible things
for dear sister Amy?

06:18.712 --> 06:21.649
Terrible things.

06:27.555 --> 06:29.089
No secrets.

06:29.122 --> 06:32.793
Those were just thoughts.

06:32.826 --> 06:34.061
They were...

06:35.896 --> 06:37.865
You hated her.

06:37.898 --> 06:41.368
You wished her dead
for calling you insane.

06:41.401 --> 06:44.371
Her foot always on your back,
stopping you from being

06:44.404 --> 06:47.641
who you are, what you could be.

06:47.675 --> 06:51.712
And now, it's time
for them to pay.

06:51.745 --> 06:54.414
Who?

06:54.448 --> 06:56.416
Everyone.

06:56.450 --> 06:58.952
Remove your mask.

06:58.986 --> 07:01.054
Show them your face.

07:01.088 --> 07:03.123
You could be beautiful.

07:04.492 --> 07:06.794
I'm not like you.

07:06.827 --> 07:08.896
I don't hide behind masks.

07:17.538 --> 07:20.674
I'm tired of the boo-hoo.

07:20.708 --> 07:22.610
Do what you want.

07:22.643 --> 07:25.112
Take what you want.

07:25.145 --> 07:28.115
Gods make rules.

07:28.148 --> 07:30.984
They don't follow them.

07:33.621 --> 07:37.090
I'm done.

07:37.124 --> 07:42.796
You and me, we're not friends.

07:42.830 --> 07:46.767
I'm not helping you anymore.

07:46.800 --> 07:50.771
I'm gonna find your body,
and then I'm gonna burn it.

07:50.804 --> 07:55.609
And if you're lucky,
that's all I'm gonna do to it.

07:55.643 --> 07:58.011
You feel me?

08:00.881 --> 08:03.784
Okay.

08:03.817 --> 08:07.955
It seems I was wrong.

08:07.988 --> 08:11.792
You're not ready
to sit with big boys.

08:11.825 --> 08:14.795
Back to the kiddie table.

08:14.828 --> 08:16.830
I will miss you, my friend.

08:16.864 --> 08:19.132
But I'm sure we will
see each other again,

08:19.166 --> 08:20.968
when I'm back in my body.

08:21.001 --> 08:23.070
My temple.

08:24.504 --> 08:26.473
On your mark,

08:26.506 --> 08:28.909
get set...

08:31.511 --> 08:32.980
...go.

08:58.271 --> 09:00.207
