Amy.

09:06.814 --> 09:08.816
Amy.

09:10.884 --> 09:12.686
It's not true.

09:12.720 --> 09:14.688
What he said.

09:14.722 --> 09:18.558
I didn't want this.

09:18.592 --> 09:20.594
I didn't...

09:25.298 --> 09:27.267
:
I'm sorry.

09:35.776 --> 09:37.778
DAVID:
Don't laugh at me.

09:39.246 --> 09:41.982
Stop it.

09:43.183 --> 09:45.919
Stop it!

09:45.953 --> 09:47.921
Now!

10:10.143 --> 10:11.779
DAVID 1:
Stop it. We can't torture him.

10:11.812 --> 10:13.280
DAVID 2:
Why not?

10:13.313 --> 10:15.282
DAVID 1:
Because first, it's horrible,

10:15.315 --> 10:17.685
and second, he's just a mind.
Does he even feel pain?

10:17.718 --> 10:19.586
SYD:
Do you want to talk about it?

10:19.619 --> 10:21.755
Huh?

10:21.789 --> 10:23.791
Amy?

10:27.194 --> 10:28.762
No.

10:28.796 --> 10:32.933
He wants you distracted,
emotional.

10:32.966 --> 10:34.101
Farouk.

10:34.134 --> 10:37.104
I know.

10:37.137 --> 10:38.638
You can't let him.

10:38.672 --> 10:40.007
I know.

11:00.694 --> 11:04.297
What does she say about it?

11:04.331 --> 11:07.067
Me, in the future.

11:10.771 --> 11:13.974
I don't know,
we haven't talked about it.

11:14.007 --> 11:15.709
Maybe you should.

11:15.743 --> 11:18.111
Talk to her.

11:19.346 --> 11:22.783
If you're not gonna talk to me.

11:26.119 --> 11:27.988
That wouldn't bother you?

11:28.021 --> 11:29.990
What?

11:30.023 --> 11:31.725
If you talk to me?

11:31.759 --> 11:33.727
In the future

11:33.761 --> 11:36.063
Oh, no reason. Just...

11:36.096 --> 11:40.400
Well, I wouldn't
want you to be jealous.

11:40.433 --> 11:42.936
Of myself?

11:42.970 --> 11:46.373
Why would I...

11:46.406 --> 11:48.075
David, why would I be
jealous of myself?

11:48.108 --> 11:50.077
No, no reason. It's...

11:50.110 --> 11:51.879
I

11:51.912 --> 11:55.382
Y-You're you and she's also you,

11:55.415 --> 11:57.417
and I'm not...

11:57.450 --> 12:00.353
It's not like
there's a handbook.

12:00.387 --> 12:02.990
Are you physical with her?

12:04.057 --> 12:05.392
No.

12:08.796 --> 12:10.363
David?

12:10.397 --> 12:13.033
See? You are jealous.

12:13.066 --> 12:14.935
I'm not.

12:17.404 --> 12:19.139
I just...

12:21.274 --> 12:23.944
You're right, it's weird.

12:25.145 --> 12:27.247
So let's...

12:27.280 --> 12:29.716
why don't we make some...

12:29.749 --> 12:31.418
ground rules?

12:35.288 --> 12:36.857
Okay.

12:39.259 --> 12:41.829
You can talk to her.

12:41.862 --> 12:45.132
And if she needs a hug
or something...

12:47.134 --> 12:50.137
I know it
doesn't make sense, but...

12:50.170 --> 12:52.472
It's-it's how you feel.

12:55.275 --> 12:57.945
Hey.

12:57.978 --> 13:00.213
I love you.

13:12.525 --> 13:15.095
Are you gonna say it, too?

13:15.128 --> 13:16.796
:
Shut up.

13:22.035 --> 13:24.304
I love you.

13:29.242 --> 13:31.244
*

14:24.197 --> 14:26.599
David?

14:40.147 --> 14:41.915
-How...
-You think he is

14:41.949 --> 14:45.118
the only one
who can outsmart the universe?

14:45.152 --> 14:46.553
Our David?

14:56.163 --> 14:58.898
:
He told you.

14:58.932 --> 15:01.468
He-- he won't help.

15:01.501 --> 15:04.137
You think I need his help?

15:07.074 --> 15:09.876
He kills you.

15:09.909 --> 15:12.045
In my timeline,
the race ends and you lose.

15:12.079 --> 15:13.380
So, yes...

15:13.413 --> 15:15.182
I think you need him.

15:18.251 --> 15:21.621
*

15:21.654 --> 15:25.558
Do you play craps?

15:25.592 --> 15:27.995
Roll the bones?

15:29.196 --> 15:31.398
Dice.

15:31.431 --> 15:34.467
A game of chance.

15:34.501 --> 15:37.437
Probabilité.

15:37.470 --> 15:39.973
But it can be rigged.

15:40.007 --> 15:41.975
You mean you can cheat?

15:42.009 --> 15:43.576
Escheat.

15:43.610 --> 15:45.345
That's a legal term...

15:45.378 --> 15:47.981
which means: under the law,

15:48.015 --> 15:50.250
the property of an individual

15:50.283 --> 15:53.020
reverts to the state

15:53.053 --> 15:57.624
if the individual dies
without an heir.

15:57.657 --> 15:59.426
I don't understand.

15:59.459 --> 16:01.161
All I'm saying is...

16:01.194 --> 16:03.030
who writes the law?

16:03.063 --> 16:04.998
The state.

16:05.032 --> 16:07.034
So you see...

16:07.067 --> 16:10.303
the game is rigged.

16:10.337 --> 16:12.172
And, baby...

16:12.205 --> 16:15.108
I am the state.

16:15.142 --> 16:17.577
So even when I lose...

16:19.512 --> 16:21.614
...I win.

16:25.418 --> 16:29.122
You can't hurt me here.

16:29.156 --> 16:31.158
You know that, right?

16:32.192 --> 16:34.061
Are you sure?

16:37.664 --> 16:40.467
But no, mon amour.

16:40.500 --> 16:43.336
Why would I hurt you?

16:44.371 --> 16:46.306
We are allies.

16:46.339 --> 16:48.708
We both want the same thing--

16:48.741 --> 16:51.044
for me to live.

16:51.078 --> 16:53.480
Now, I know why this

16:53.513 --> 16:56.316
is what I want.

16:56.349 --> 16:58.051
The question is:

16:58.085 --> 17:01.654
why is this what you want?

17:01.688 --> 17:04.557
We need you.

17:05.558 --> 17:07.527
We?

17:12.199 --> 17:14.301
I need you.

17:15.635 --> 17:19.106
To stop the world from ending.

17:21.541 --> 17:25.378
And who will end the world?

17:28.115 --> 17:31.050
Tiny humans with their bombs?

17:31.084 --> 17:33.453
Or World War III?

17:37.224 --> 17:38.558
No.

17:39.759 --> 17:41.761
*

17:55.742 --> 17:57.610
No.

18:07.120 --> 18:08.421
Stop it.

18:14.093 --> 18:16.496
For centuries...

18:16.529 --> 18:19.666
everyone said, "Amahl Farouk

18:19.699 --> 18:21.568
is the villain."

18:21.601 --> 18:23.670
Year after year,

18:23.703 --> 18:26.739
they came-- the heroes...

18:26.773 --> 18:31.077
with their blue eyes
and their white skin...

18:31.110 --> 18:32.779
to kill me.

18:35.282 --> 18:38.685
They thought by killing me

18:38.718 --> 18:41.788
they will save the world.

18:41.821 --> 18:44.791
And now you're telling me

18:44.824 --> 18:48.628
that the opposite is true.

18:48.661 --> 18:50.463
That...

18:50.497 --> 18:52.799
the villain...

18:52.832 --> 18:55.768
is the hero...

18:55.802 --> 18:58.771
and the hero...

18:58.805 --> 19:01.341
is the villain?

19:06.813 --> 19:09.316
Oxymoron.

19:11.184 --> 19:14.354
Maybe we're all
vill-villains.

19:14.387 --> 19:16.356
All?

19:16.389 --> 19:18.358
If you're the Earth,

19:18.391 --> 19:21.494
the birds...

19:21.528 --> 19:23.330
peace.

19:27.334 --> 19:31.137
"When two tribes go to war...

19:31.170 --> 19:34.507
a point is all you can score."

19:35.675 --> 19:38.678
Frankie Goes to Hollywood.

19:41.881 --> 19:44.751
If David doesn't help me...

19:47.287 --> 19:49.188
...you will.

19:50.523 --> 19:54.694
And together,
we'll rule the world.

19:56.596 --> 19:58.765
Save the world.

20:00.199 --> 20:02.235
From him.

20:58.257 --> 21:02.629
Isn't it weird that
we were both inside David?

21:02.662 --> 21:04.531
Mentally, I mean.

21:05.598 --> 21:07.934
I know what you're doing.

21:07.967 --> 21:09.636
What?

21:09.669 --> 21:12.639
Shaving my armpits?

21:12.672 --> 21:14.741
You're not Lenny.

21:14.774 --> 21:17.444
And you're not Amy.

21:17.477 --> 21:20.347
You're the song they play
outside a hostage crisis

21:20.380 --> 21:24.417
to keep criminals
from thinking clearly.

21:25.985 --> 21:28.355
I hear what you're saying.

21:28.388 --> 21:30.490
And I agree--

21:30.523 --> 21:32.692
we're gonna be best friends.

21:32.725 --> 21:34.894
It's not gonna work.

21:36.496 --> 21:39.532
None of your crazy shit.

21:39.566 --> 21:43.770
Whatever Farouk
told you to do...

21:43.803 --> 21:46.272
your secret plan...

21:46.305 --> 21:48.708
it's just noise.

21:52.979 --> 21:54.914
He raped me.

21:56.749 --> 21:58.385
Farouk.

21:58.418 --> 22:00.453
Over and over again.

22:00.487 --> 22:04.290
Kept me in the basement
of his mind.

22:04.323 --> 22:06.359
Like one of those Amish girls

22:06.393 --> 22:09.028
snatched from the side
of the road.

22:14.367 --> 22:15.402
But...

22:15.435 --> 22:16.969
you know, whatever.

22:17.003 --> 22:20.473
Um, bros before hos, right?

22:20.507 --> 22:23.376
:
Girl power. I guess.

